WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.280 --> 00:00:09.573
Everlight?

2
00:00:11.158 --> 00:00:14.118
Everlight. it-it's me.

3
00:00:14.119 --> 00:00:15.370
Pike.

4
00:00:20.917 --> 00:00:24.712
If I've ever needed you. it's now.

5
00:00:24.713 --> 00:00:27.299
Pike Trickfoot.

6
00:00:32.179 --> 00:00:35.014
I felt weak the moment
we entered the Hells.

7
00:00:35.015 --> 00:00:37.475
I-I need to know you're still...

8
00:00:37.476 --> 00:00:39.477
{\an8}Child.
redemption does not exist

9
00:00:39.478 --> 00:00:41.395
{\an8}in the realm of the damned.

10
00:00:41.396 --> 00:00:44.440
The Hells of Despath are forbidden.

11
00:00:44.441 --> 00:00:46.066
But why?

12
00:00:46.067 --> 00:00:49.236
If we find Zerxus.
we'll-we'll get the vestige we need.

13
00:00:49.237 --> 00:00:52.198
Your soul is precious.

14
00:00:52.199 --> 00:00:54.158
There are those in Hell who would use it

15
00:00:54.159 --> 00:00:56.035
for wicked aims.

16
00:00:56.036 --> 00:00:57.912
Ignore my words

17
00:00:57.913 --> 00:01:02.041
and you will find yourself alone.

18
00:01:02.042 --> 00:01:03.877
What does that mean?

19
00:01:04.920 --> 00:01:06.295
Everlight?

20
00:01:06.296 --> 00:01:08.715
Wait! Please!

21
00:01:12.302 --> 00:01:15.889
Pike...

22
00:01:17.766 --> 00:01:19.266
<i>Pike?</i>

23
00:01:19.267 --> 00:01:21.227
Pike?

24
00:01:21.228 --> 00:01:23.771
I was calling your name.

25
00:01:23.772 --> 00:01:26.232
Oh. I-I was just...

26
00:01:26.233 --> 00:01:28.901
making sure we're being looked out for.

27
00:01:28.902 --> 00:01:31.570
Oh. Your goddess got our backs?

28
00:01:31.571 --> 00:01:32.988
Yeah.

29
00:01:32.989 --> 00:01:34.615
Sure does.

30
00:01:34.616 --> 00:01:36.367
Good.

31
00:01:36.368 --> 00:01:37.785
'Cause to pull this off...

32
00:01:37.786 --> 00:01:41.832
we're gonna need
all kinds of miracles.

33
00:03:19.095 --> 00:03:20.971
There it is.

34
00:03:20.972 --> 00:03:22.890
The City of Dis.

35
00:03:22.891 --> 00:03:24.099
Um. okay.

36
00:03:24.100 --> 00:03:25.601
how are we gonna do this?

37
00:03:25.602 --> 00:03:27.186
Everyone down there is either a demon

38
00:03:27.187 --> 00:03:29.355
or is getting eaten by one.

39
00:03:29.356 --> 00:03:32.317
Well. we certainly don't look
like we belong in Hell.

40
00:03:34.778 --> 00:03:36.153
Unless we did.

41
00:03:36.154 --> 00:03:37.821
Little man?

42
00:03:37.822 --> 00:03:40.075
Huh? Oh. right.

43
00:03:46.331 --> 00:03:47.706
Whoa.

44
00:03:47.707 --> 00:03:48.874
Fuck yes.

45
00:03:48.875 --> 00:03:50.334
Bigger antlers.

46
00:03:50.335 --> 00:03:52.628
Wha... A bunny? Come on!

47
00:03:52.629 --> 00:03:53.712
Hey. just kidding.

48
00:03:53.713 --> 00:03:54.798
Just kidding. buddy.

49
00:03:56.716 --> 00:03:57.758
How's this feel?

50
00:03:57.759 --> 00:04:00.679
Wicked.

51
00:04:03.098 --> 00:04:04.808
Pike.

52
00:04:08.228 --> 00:04:09.229
<i>Come.</i>

53
00:04:10.230 --> 00:04:12.023
Uh. you okay?

54
00:04:13.108 --> 00:04:14.733
Those souls...

55
00:04:14.734 --> 00:04:16.527
I wish I could help them.

56
00:04:16.528 --> 00:04:18.612
Maybe Keyleth was right.

57
00:04:18.613 --> 00:04:22.032
Is going through Hell worth it
for one vestige?

58
00:04:22.033 --> 00:04:25.160
You heard Raishan.
We'll never defeat Thordak without it.

59
00:04:25.161 --> 00:04:28.747
Everything about this place
just feels wrong.

60
00:04:28.748 --> 00:04:30.958
Like being here is a sin.

61
00:04:30.959 --> 00:04:34.045
I don't think we can turn back.

62
00:04:35.130 --> 00:04:38.048
Hey. it's gonna be okay. buddies.

63
00:04:38.049 --> 00:04:40.217
Hell ain't such a bad place.

64
00:04:40.218 --> 00:04:43.054
I mean. lots of people
have told me to go here.

65
00:04:44.472 --> 00:04:45.764
We need to move. people.

66
00:04:45.765 --> 00:04:48.476
Scanlan's spell won't last forever.

67
00:04:49.644 --> 00:04:51.104
Forgive me.

68
00:05:06.077 --> 00:05:08.245
You there.

69
00:05:08.246 --> 00:05:10.789
You don't look familiar.

70
00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:13.001
Where are you going?

71
00:05:14.085 --> 00:05:15.586
Oh.

72
00:05:15.587 --> 00:05:19.131
Um. the fallen soul
of Zerxus Ilerez

73
00:05:19.132 --> 00:05:20.674
owes us a debt.

74
00:05:20.675 --> 00:05:22.969
And we plan on collecting.

75
00:05:24.387 --> 00:05:26.096
Really?

76
00:05:26.097 --> 00:05:29.684
You lot are bold enough to see him?

77
00:05:37.817 --> 00:05:39.110
The fuck?

78
00:05:40.528 --> 00:05:42.279
Hmm.

79
00:05:42.280 --> 00:05:44.115
Very well.

80
00:05:50.163 --> 00:05:51.247
Ugh. that was gross.

81
00:05:51.915 --> 00:05:53.917
Order up!

82
00:06:00.173 --> 00:06:02.382
Who's next. then?

83
00:06:02.383 --> 00:06:05.803
You smell... different.

84
00:06:05.804 --> 00:06:08.514
Oh. uh. we haven't bathed

85
00:06:08.515 --> 00:06:11.267
in a few thousand years.

86
00:06:13.686 --> 00:06:14.686
Um. excu...

87
00:06:14.687 --> 00:06:17.356
Excuse me.

88
00:06:17.357 --> 00:06:20.359
Do you know where we can find
the Brass Skull?

89
00:06:20.360 --> 00:06:24.656
We're looking for someone named Zerxus.

90
00:06:31.538 --> 00:06:33.414
They were scared of his name.

91
00:06:36.251 --> 00:06:37.544
<i>Find me.</i>

92
00:06:41.131 --> 00:06:43.132
Let's get moving.

93
00:06:43.133 --> 00:06:45.175
Don't want to be here
longer than we have to.

94
00:06:45.176 --> 00:06:47.052
Well. at least Team Draconia

95
00:06:47.053 --> 00:06:49.472
is having a nice.
quiet time in the snow.

96
00:07:00.108 --> 00:07:03.277
I still maintain it would have
been safer to drill our way out.

97
00:07:03.278 --> 00:07:05.320
Yes. but my way was cooler.

98
00:07:05.321 --> 00:07:06.739
I could have made it cool.

99
00:07:07.782 --> 00:07:12.536
Kima? Can you hear me?

100
00:07:12.537 --> 00:07:14.622
Kima!

101
00:07:15.748 --> 00:07:16.999
She can't be far.

102
00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:18.458
What do you want to do?

103
00:07:18.459 --> 00:07:23.381
I'm going to tear
that fucking dragon to pieces.

104
00:07:33.308 --> 00:07:34.683
Whoa. Pike.

105
00:07:34.684 --> 00:07:36.477
You look like hell. even for a demon.

106
00:07:37.896 --> 00:07:40.397
I think I'll wait here a sec.

107
00:07:40.398 --> 00:07:43.066
You guys keep searching.

108
00:07:43.067 --> 00:07:46.112
It-It's fine. I-I'll be okay.

109
00:07:47.155 --> 00:07:50.240
Spread out. Don't go too far. though.

110
00:07:50.241 --> 00:07:52.869
Don't like the way
these creatures are looking at us.

111
00:07:57.832 --> 00:07:59.875
All this evil.

112
00:07:59.876 --> 00:08:02.002
Maybe the Everlight was right.

113
00:08:02.003 --> 00:08:04.047
We shouldn't be here.

114
00:08:16.976 --> 00:08:18.810
It-It's all right.

115
00:08:18.811 --> 00:08:21.605
I... I won't hurt you.

116
00:08:21.606 --> 00:08:23.942
I only want to help.

117
00:08:25.068 --> 00:08:26.610
Please.

118
00:08:26.611 --> 00:08:29.697
Redeem this woman
with your healing light.

119
00:08:35.495 --> 00:08:37.204
Pike!

120
00:08:37.205 --> 00:08:38.747
What's happening?

121
00:08:38.748 --> 00:08:40.290
Hurts my brain!

122
00:08:40.291 --> 00:08:42.501
Shit. Scanlan. the spell?

123
00:08:42.502 --> 00:08:44.963
{\an8}I can't concentrate
with all this screaming!

124
00:08:48.883 --> 00:08:50.468
Mortals.

125
00:08:52.595 --> 00:08:54.721
Fresh blood.

126
00:08:54.722 --> 00:08:56.556
We can't stay here.

127
00:08:56.557 --> 00:08:58.101
Don't need to ask me twice.

128
00:09:01.187 --> 00:09:03.273
Gotta move. Pikey.

129
00:09:04.983 --> 00:09:06.150
Shit.

130
00:09:12.699 --> 00:09:15.784
Where is this fucking Brass Skull?

131
00:09:15.785 --> 00:09:17.577
We can't outrun an entire city.

132
00:09:17.578 --> 00:09:19.079
We gotta get back to the portal.

133
00:09:19.080 --> 00:09:20.707
Not without the armor.

134
00:09:22.500 --> 00:09:25.085
They got eyes in the sky.
What are we doing?

135
00:09:25.086 --> 00:09:26.879
<i>This way.</i>

136
00:09:28.214 --> 00:09:30.466
Guys. down there.

137
00:09:33.052 --> 00:09:36.263
Yes! Good eyes. buddies!

138
00:09:36.264 --> 00:09:38.182
Get ready to jump!

139
00:09:59.495 --> 00:10:02.914
Fuck me. it's gonna be close!

140
00:10:02.915 --> 00:10:04.584
<i>Enter.</i>

141
00:10:23.644 --> 00:10:25.854
Thanks for helping us.

142
00:10:25.855 --> 00:10:27.981
I-I hope?

143
00:10:27.982 --> 00:10:30.360
This way.

144
00:10:35.406 --> 00:10:37.700
What is this place?

145
00:10:38.993 --> 00:10:40.035
Whoa.

146
00:10:40.036 --> 00:10:42.205
Uh. neat trick?

147
00:10:43.331 --> 00:10:44.748
Vox Machina.

148
00:10:44.749 --> 00:10:48.001
You certainly know
how to make an entrance.

149
00:10:48.002 --> 00:10:50.253
How did you know we were coming?

150
00:10:50.254 --> 00:10:53.006
"Speak of the devil
and he shall appear."

151
00:10:53.007 --> 00:10:56.551
The rules of this realm are... unique.

152
00:10:56.552 --> 00:11:00.097
I'd urge caution
before uttering further names.

153
00:11:00.098 --> 00:11:02.516
You were the presence I felt.

154
00:11:02.517 --> 00:11:05.227
W-Why did you reach out to me?

155
00:11:05.228 --> 00:11:07.187
The real question is

156
00:11:07.188 --> 00:11:10.024
what is a priest
of the Everlight doing here?

157
00:11:11.526 --> 00:11:13.985
We were sent by J'mon Sa Ord.

158
00:11:13.986 --> 00:11:15.529
They left something with you.

159
00:11:15.530 --> 00:11:17.572
The Plate of the Dawnmartyr?

160
00:11:17.573 --> 00:11:20.575
Not left. Lost.

161
00:11:20.576 --> 00:11:22.994
What do you mean. "lost"?

162
00:11:22.995 --> 00:11:25.205
Every decade or so. J'mon comes to test

163
00:11:25.206 --> 00:11:27.541
their rather poor luck at my table.

164
00:11:27.542 --> 00:11:32.129
They shouldn't have wagered
such an artifact. but fair's fair.

165
00:11:32.130 --> 00:11:34.798
I assume you have something
to exchange for it?

166
00:11:34.799 --> 00:11:39.011
I know you didn't venture into Hell
with no more than wishful thinking.

167
00:11:40.138 --> 00:11:41.805
Well. what sort of stuff

168
00:11:41.806 --> 00:11:44.975
does a devil dude want? Gold?

169
00:11:44.976 --> 00:11:46.810
For a vestige?

170
00:11:46.811 --> 00:11:50.856
No. you'd have to
make an exquisite offer.

171
00:11:50.857 --> 00:11:52.774
Or wager.

172
00:11:52.775 --> 00:11:54.944
Care for a game of chance?

173
00:11:56.154 --> 00:11:59.114
If we win. we get the Plate.

174
00:11:59.115 --> 00:12:00.699
And if I win.

175
00:12:00.700 --> 00:12:02.659
you stay as my guest.

176
00:12:02.660 --> 00:12:04.619
Indefinitely.

177
00:12:04.620 --> 00:12:06.663
Pike. you can't. He'll cheat.

178
00:12:06.664 --> 00:12:07.998
Now. now.

179
00:12:07.999 --> 00:12:10.000
Rules are what separates Despath

180
00:12:10.001 --> 00:12:13.628
from the truly miserable
planes of existence like yours.

181
00:12:13.629 --> 00:12:16.299
No cheating allowed.

182
00:12:17.300 --> 00:12:20.595
Okay. What's the game?

183
00:12:25.224 --> 00:12:26.601
Uh. what the...

184
00:12:30.354 --> 00:12:31.481
Huh?

185
00:12:33.649 --> 00:12:35.860
- Huh?
- Pike?

186
00:12:39.197 --> 00:12:41.073
Have a seat.

187
00:12:44.577 --> 00:12:45.702
A contract?

188
00:12:45.703 --> 00:12:48.831
To ensure you don't get cold feet.

189
00:12:49.957 --> 00:12:51.166
Are they...

190
00:12:51.167 --> 00:12:53.084
Safe. but silenced.

191
00:12:53.085 --> 00:12:54.920
So the game remains fair.

192
00:12:54.921 --> 00:12:57.256
Shall we?

193
00:13:11.479 --> 00:13:14.022
Such pure blood.

194
00:13:14.023 --> 00:13:16.025
Quite special. really.

195
00:13:22.823 --> 00:13:24.533
The game is "Five Skulls."

196
00:13:24.534 --> 00:13:26.159
Each player has five cards.

197
00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:28.912
consisting of four red
and a single black skull.

198
00:13:28.913 --> 00:13:31.122
Once dealt. you may not move your cards

199
00:13:31.123 --> 00:13:32.791
nor touch your opponent's.

200
00:13:32.792 --> 00:13:34.751
Your goal is to find my black skull

201
00:13:34.752 --> 00:13:36.002
before I find yours.

202
00:13:36.003 --> 00:13:37.254
How?

203
00:13:37.255 --> 00:13:38.838
On each turn you may ask your opponent

204
00:13:38.839 --> 00:13:40.632
any question to help locate it.

205
00:13:40.633 --> 00:13:45.345
However. you must answer
all questions truthfully

206
00:13:45.346 --> 00:13:47.515
or incur a steep penalty.

207
00:13:48.975 --> 00:13:52.310
Like I said. we have rules down here.

208
00:13:52.311 --> 00:13:56.648
Damn. they got some
plush chairs in this bitch.

209
00:13:56.649 --> 00:13:58.817
I can't believe she's doing this.

210
00:13:58.818 --> 00:14:01.444
Hey. if anyone can see through
a devil's scheme.

211
00:14:01.445 --> 00:14:02.696
it's Trickfoot.

212
00:14:02.697 --> 00:14:05.824
Going first obviously
has its advantages.

213
00:14:05.825 --> 00:14:07.409
As you are my guest.

214
00:14:07.410 --> 00:14:09.287
you may do the honors.

215
00:14:15.293 --> 00:14:17.336
First question is yours.

216
00:14:18.337 --> 00:14:21.840
Okay. let's whittle this down.

217
00:14:21.841 --> 00:14:24.092
Is your black skull to the right

218
00:14:24.093 --> 00:14:26.678
or left of your middle card?

219
00:14:26.679 --> 00:14:29.139
You can't feel the presence
of the Everlight.

220
00:14:29.140 --> 00:14:31.517
Your redeemer isn't here. is she?

221
00:14:32.977 --> 00:14:35.438
That wasn't my question.

222
00:14:37.023 --> 00:14:38.524
To the right.

223
00:14:39.859 --> 00:14:41.401
On the end.

224
00:14:41.402 --> 00:14:43.153
That's your card.

225
00:14:43.154 --> 00:14:46.032
Sadly. no.

226
00:14:48.075 --> 00:14:51.578
Though I think I learned more
that round than you did.

227
00:14:51.579 --> 00:14:55.165
After all. everyone has a tell.

228
00:14:55.166 --> 00:14:57.250
If you dig deep enough.

229
00:14:57.251 --> 00:15:00.337
Aren't you going to ask me something?

230
00:15:00.338 --> 00:15:02.589
Your friends rely on you.

231
00:15:02.590 --> 00:15:06.176
You must take pride
in always being there to save them.

232
00:15:06.177 --> 00:15:08.887
To redeem them.

233
00:15:08.888 --> 00:15:10.930
This is no card game.

234
00:15:10.931 --> 00:15:13.308
He knew exactly
who he wanted to play with.

235
00:15:13.309 --> 00:15:16.102
I'm still tryin' to
figure out the rules.

236
00:15:16.103 --> 00:15:17.771
Tell me. holy one.

237
00:15:17.772 --> 00:15:20.940
were you given a choice? A path to walk?

238
00:15:20.941 --> 00:15:22.400
W-What?

239
00:15:22.401 --> 00:15:24.444
"We do not choose..."

240
00:15:24.445 --> 00:15:27.072
<i>"...any path can be a holy one..."</i>

241
00:15:27.073 --> 00:15:31.202
<i>"...so long as one
walks it with truth."</i>

242
00:15:33.204 --> 00:15:36.998
Yes... I-I was given a choice.

243
00:15:36.999 --> 00:15:39.167
Turns out the choice was a lie.

244
00:15:39.168 --> 00:15:41.295
Both paths led to the same end.

245
00:15:42.588 --> 00:15:44.714
I once was given a similar choice.

246
00:15:44.715 --> 00:15:47.801
It cost me my family.

247
00:15:47.802 --> 00:15:52.555
My god betrayed me. as yours will. too.

248
00:15:52.556 --> 00:15:56.142
No. You're trying to get in my head.

249
00:15:56.143 --> 00:15:57.602
It's not gonna work.

250
00:15:57.603 --> 00:16:00.563
Oh. I already have what I need.

251
00:16:00.564 --> 00:16:02.524
You gave yourself away before.

252
00:16:02.525 --> 00:16:04.943
Your eyes. Your black card?

253
00:16:04.944 --> 00:16:07.238
Second from your left.

254
00:16:09.115 --> 00:16:10.574
- No!
- Buddies!

255
00:16:12.326 --> 00:16:13.743
This is bullshit!

256
00:16:13.744 --> 00:16:16.079
Changing the subject like that?
Y-You're cheating!

257
00:16:16.080 --> 00:16:19.416
How? All the answers were truthful.

258
00:16:19.417 --> 00:16:21.918
Contract or no. this is a farce.

259
00:16:21.919 --> 00:16:23.920
Needle-dick is right.

260
00:16:23.921 --> 00:16:25.797
I ain't watchin' this no more!

261
00:16:25.798 --> 00:16:27.383
Wait. maybe you shouldn't...

262
00:16:29.552 --> 00:16:32.930
Stupid comfortable chair!

263
00:16:33.931 --> 00:16:37.517
Pike Trickfoot. you are now
bound to this sanctum

264
00:16:37.518 --> 00:16:40.395
and the service of the Fallen Knight

265
00:16:40.396 --> 00:16:42.272
for eternity.

266
00:16:42.273 --> 00:16:44.357
Wait. I-I... Please.

267
00:16:44.358 --> 00:16:46.067
You have to give me another chance.

268
00:16:46.068 --> 00:16:49.405
What else might you have
to offer at this point?

269
00:16:53.200 --> 00:16:55.952
What? She can't!

270
00:16:55.953 --> 00:16:58.329
A meaningful wager. indeed.

271
00:16:58.330 --> 00:17:00.957
Alas. I have no use for it.

272
00:17:00.958 --> 00:17:02.500
For the Plate of the Dawnmartyr.

273
00:17:02.501 --> 00:17:05.421
I will require something
more substantial...

274
00:17:06.172 --> 00:17:08.506
The souls of your friends.

275
00:17:08.507 --> 00:17:10.967
No. not them. I can't.

276
00:17:10.968 --> 00:17:13.304
Isn't your faith strong enough?

277
00:17:19.310 --> 00:17:20.560
Fine.

278
00:17:20.561 --> 00:17:23.063
One round. Winner takes all.

279
00:17:27.067 --> 00:17:30.111
Wait. Are we the ante?

280
00:17:30.112 --> 00:17:32.322
Sure feels like it.
Is she crazy?

281
00:17:32.323 --> 00:17:35.034
Um. Pikey?

282
00:17:36.911 --> 00:17:39.579
I can see why the Everlight favors you.

283
00:17:39.580 --> 00:17:41.247
You're as careless
with those close to you

284
00:17:41.248 --> 00:17:43.249
as you are yourself.

285
00:17:43.250 --> 00:17:46.670
But this time. I'll go first.

286
00:17:48.547 --> 00:17:51.549
My turn. my question.

287
00:17:51.550 --> 00:17:55.178
There's something
different about you. Pike.

288
00:17:55.179 --> 00:17:57.347
You're special.

289
00:17:57.348 --> 00:18:00.225
Have you ever wondered
if the Everlight needs you...

290
00:18:00.226 --> 00:18:02.268
more than you need her?

291
00:18:02.269 --> 00:18:04.563
Never crossed my mind.

292
00:18:05.815 --> 00:18:07.357
Two cards?

293
00:18:07.358 --> 00:18:09.067
Lying to yourself.

294
00:18:09.068 --> 00:18:11.486
Goodness. that's a new one.

295
00:18:11.487 --> 00:18:13.029
That's not fair!

296
00:18:13.030 --> 00:18:15.156
The truth rarely is.

297
00:18:15.157 --> 00:18:17.075
You've made it easier for me.

298
00:18:17.076 --> 00:18:19.119
Reveal the card on my right.

299
00:18:24.500 --> 00:18:26.376
Pity. Your turn.

300
00:18:26.377 --> 00:18:28.419
Okay. cut the shit.

301
00:18:28.420 --> 00:18:30.630
Which card is your black skull?

302
00:18:30.631 --> 00:18:32.423
Interesting approach.

303
00:18:32.424 --> 00:18:34.759
Since I cannot lie. I'll tell you.

304
00:18:34.760 --> 00:18:37.054
It's the one in my hand.

305
00:18:38.764 --> 00:18:40.224
Far left.

306
00:18:44.019 --> 00:18:48.648
Two cards. What to ask next.

307
00:18:48.649 --> 00:18:50.401
Ah. I've got it.

308
00:18:51.944 --> 00:18:53.903
Do you ever wonder
if your life would be better

309
00:18:53.904 --> 00:18:55.531
without the Everlight?

310
00:18:58.367 --> 00:19:00.159
Yes.

311
00:19:00.160 --> 00:19:02.829
Doesn't sound very "faithful" to me.

312
00:19:02.830 --> 00:19:05.416
Your left card.

313
00:19:08.377 --> 00:19:11.129
Looks like the game is almost over.

314
00:19:11.130 --> 00:19:14.007
Oh. shit.

315
00:19:14.008 --> 00:19:17.093
Before you finish me off.

316
00:19:17.094 --> 00:19:19.470
do me one favor.

317
00:19:19.471 --> 00:19:22.640
If you're keeping me here for eternity.

318
00:19:22.641 --> 00:19:25.602
I think I deserve to know who you are.

319
00:19:25.603 --> 00:19:28.021
Who you were.

320
00:19:28.022 --> 00:19:31.191
And why you chose me.

321
00:19:32.735 --> 00:19:37.031
Very well.
Treat this as a last indulgence.

322
00:19:38.407 --> 00:19:42.160
I come from a time a thousand years ago.

323
00:19:42.161 --> 00:19:45.455
<i>when gods walked amongst mortals.</i>

324
00:19:45.456 --> 00:19:48.166
<i>And the world was ruled by magic.</i>

325
00:19:48.167 --> 00:19:51.836
<i>Like you. I protected
my home as First Knight.</i>

326
00:19:51.837 --> 00:19:53.755
<i>a member of the Brass Ring.</i>

327
00:19:53.756 --> 00:19:57.383
<i>a group similar to yours.</i>

328
00:19:57.384 --> 00:20:01.304
<i>And also like you.
I assumed the best in them.</i>

329
00:20:01.305 --> 00:20:05.725
<i>I was blind as my friends condemned
our civilization with their curiosity.</i>

330
00:20:05.726 --> 00:20:07.353
<i>Their hubris.</i>

331
00:20:09.855 --> 00:20:13.274
You mean... the Calamity?

332
00:20:13.275 --> 00:20:16.361
The gods set to war upon Exandria.

333
00:20:16.362 --> 00:20:18.363
and in the chaos I found myself

334
00:20:18.364 --> 00:20:23.368
<i>face-to-face
with the Lord of Torment himself.</i>

335
00:20:23.369 --> 00:20:25.745
<i>But instead of destroying me.</i>

336
00:20:25.746 --> 00:20:28.665
<i>he gave me a choice.</i>

337
00:20:28.666 --> 00:20:32.001
<i>Die with the rest or join him.</i>

338
00:20:32.002 --> 00:20:33.753
and spare my family.

339
00:20:33.754 --> 00:20:36.089
I thought if I had enough time.

340
00:20:36.090 --> 00:20:38.633
I could reach him. save him.

341
00:20:38.634 --> 00:20:41.219
tame his turbulent heart.

342
00:20:41.220 --> 00:20:45.765
<i>For my folly. I watched
my husband and son</i>

343
00:20:45.766 --> 00:20:48.434
<i>fade with the rigors of time.</i>

344
00:20:48.435 --> 00:20:51.604
<i>losing even the memory of me.</i>

345
00:20:51.605 --> 00:20:54.857
As if I never existed at all.

346
00:20:54.858 --> 00:20:57.568
You trusted a Betrayer?

347
00:20:57.569 --> 00:20:59.070
Of course I did.

348
00:20:59.071 --> 00:21:02.198
Just like you foolishly trust
your Everlight.

349
00:21:02.199 --> 00:21:05.827
But there is no difference
between the gods above and below.

350
00:21:05.828 --> 00:21:08.038
They all lie!

351
00:21:13.293 --> 00:21:16.629
I'm sorry for all you've lost.

352
00:21:16.630 --> 00:21:18.631
But my friends aren't like that.

353
00:21:18.632 --> 00:21:20.341
And neither is my god.

354
00:21:20.342 --> 00:21:22.552
Give it time.

355
00:21:22.553 --> 00:21:25.680
Now. we have a game to finish.

356
00:21:25.681 --> 00:21:28.058
And you have a question to ask.

357
00:21:29.184 --> 00:21:32.687
Okay. I think I have it.

358
00:21:32.688 --> 00:21:36.024
Do you wish your family was here?

359
00:21:36.025 --> 00:21:38.234
What?

360
00:21:38.235 --> 00:21:42.530
You chose this existence
to spare your husband and child.

361
00:21:42.531 --> 00:21:46.451
You say you loved them.
but all I hear is regret.

362
00:21:46.452 --> 00:21:50.830
So. do you want them
with you in this nightmare?

363
00:21:50.831 --> 00:21:52.999
Or is that too selfish?

364
00:21:53.000 --> 00:21:55.251
I. uh...

365
00:21:55.252 --> 00:21:56.961
Answer my question.

366
00:21:56.962 --> 00:22:00.548
Do you wish they were here.
suffering with you?

367
00:22:00.549 --> 00:22:03.259
- No. I...
- Answer me!

368
00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:05.387
Of course not!

369
00:22:08.807 --> 00:22:11.476
I'm not even sure
you knew you were lying.

370
00:22:11.477 --> 00:22:12.727
No...

371
00:22:12.728 --> 00:22:15.814
And now my choice is a lot simpler.

372
00:22:18.650 --> 00:22:22.945
After all. everyone has a tell
if you dig deep enough.

373
00:22:22.946 --> 00:22:25.074
That one.

374
00:22:33.582 --> 00:22:36.667
Well played. Pike Trickfoot.

375
00:22:36.668 --> 00:22:39.629
That was more devious than I expected.

376
00:22:39.630 --> 00:22:41.631
We all have blind spots.

377
00:22:41.632 --> 00:22:42.799
Even you.

378
00:22:42.800 --> 00:22:45.593
It's rare for me to lose in my domain.

379
00:22:45.594 --> 00:22:48.889
However. I accept defeat.

380
00:22:58.315 --> 00:22:59.858
Whoa.

381
00:23:08.700 --> 00:23:12.078
Yeah. buddies! Look at that!

382
00:23:12.079 --> 00:23:14.664
Ah. thank the gods.

383
00:23:14.665 --> 00:23:17.959
So... guess the Everlight
came through. huh?

384
00:23:17.960 --> 00:23:20.419
Uh. yeah. Yeah.

385
00:23:20.420 --> 00:23:23.507
Aww. only Pike gets a souvenir?

386
00:23:25.092 --> 00:23:26.968
I won't forget your story.

387
00:23:26.969 --> 00:23:29.303
Thank you for losing graciously.

388
00:23:29.304 --> 00:23:31.140
I won't forget yours.

389
00:23:32.641 --> 00:23:36.060
Okay. Anyone else ready
to get the fuck out of here?

390
00:23:36.061 --> 00:23:37.770
So say we all.

391
00:23:37.771 --> 00:23:40.690
Here. take this. It bears my mark.

392
00:23:40.691 --> 00:23:44.110
You'll need it
to get safely through Despath.

393
00:23:44.111 --> 00:23:46.779
Yenk. show them the door.

394
00:23:46.780 --> 00:23:49.825
And please. give J'mon my best.

395
00:23:56.081 --> 00:23:59.167
She has no idea what courses
through her veins.

396
00:23:59.168 --> 00:24:02.003
No matter. the seed of doubt
has been planted

397
00:24:02.004 --> 00:24:05.506
and will fill her heart with vengeance.

398
00:24:05.507 --> 00:24:08.134
as we watch it grow.

399
00:24:08.135 --> 00:24:10.011
Your orders?

400
00:24:10.012 --> 00:24:12.471
Leave her. Kill the rest.

401
00:24:12.472 --> 00:24:14.849
We are his blood.

402
00:24:14.850 --> 00:24:19.103
The time for his ascension draws near.

403
00:24:19.104 --> 00:24:21.981
Whew. Getting out of here is gonna be
way easier than getting in.

404
00:24:21.982 --> 00:24:24.401
Good. 'cause I can't eat any more bugs.

405
00:24:26.778 --> 00:24:30.740
Oh. what are the chances
that isn't for us?

406
00:24:30.741 --> 00:24:33.493
Hmm. I say. 50-30?

407
00:24:35.787 --> 00:24:39.041
Vox Machina!

408
00:24:44.087 --> 00:24:46.798
I hate math.

409
00:25:34.930 --> 00:25:36.848
Chirp.
